    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text><![CDATA[**31.2 E1 Approximate Derivatives of Functions**

Let \\\(f(x) = {@fn@}\\\) and {@'a=a@}. Let {@'h = h@} and approximate \\\(f′(a)\\\) using forward, backward
and central diﬀerences. Specify 8 decimal places and compare your answers with the exact
result, which is {@(make_multsgn("none"), stack_disp_fractions("i"),diff(fn,x))@} at {@x=a@}. Provide absolute values of the relative error.

Numerical evaluation of the exact result:

\\\(f'(a)=\\\) [[input:S_dx]] [[validation:S_dx]] [[feedback:dx]]

Forward difference:

\\\(f'(a)_F\approx\\\) [[input:S_df]] [[validation:S_df]] [[feedback:df]]

Error: [[input:S_dfp]]% [[validation:S_dfp]] [[feedback:dfp]]

Backward difference:

\\\(f'(a)_B\approx\\\) [[input:S_db]] [[validation:S_db]] [[feedback:db]]

Error: [[input:S_dbp]]% [[validation:S_dbp]] [[feedback:dbp]]

Central difference:

\\\(f'(a)_C\approx\\\) [[input:S_dc]] [[validation:S_dc]] [[feedback:dc]]

Error: [[input:S_dcp]]% [[validation:S_dcp]] [[feedback:dcp]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
